The paper discusses clustering problems from a combinatorial viewpoint, which is closely related to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also covers various clustering algorithms and approaches to evaluation, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of optimization models, which is relevant to both optimization (cs.CC) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
